<title>UK: BOE forecasts 2.5 bln stg shortage, offers help.</title>
<headline>BOE forecasts 2.5 bln stg shortage, offers help.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Bank of England offered the UK money market an early round of assistance after forecasting a liquidity shortage of around 2.5 billion stg.</p>
<p>The operations will comprise 6.25 percent repos to June 9 and outright offers of bills maturing on or before June 9.</p>
